	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				First of all, I hope that you all noticed that &quot;Mortiz&quot; up there is not correct.  The Mortician sells a recipe for embalming fluid, not the actual fluid. It sounds like &quot;Cirax&quot; got lucky more than anything, I can't think of where those slaves might have come from to have trained on him, other than the close-by island where I found them.  Try running up and down the island, sitting in one spot won't help (if you might have thought of doing that). <BR>
Elmorte, getting the embalming fluid is the hardest part of this quest because it requires so many steps, you don't just kill something and return to the Mortician.  I didn't personally loose the powder when I tried this, so it sounds to me like you might have used the wrong combination of ingredients.  Remember that the Mortician is only important for one step: getting rubbing alcohol, and that's something you just purchace from him/it.  Embalming fluid takes bone granite powder you must smith, bog juice you must brew, and other things you buy.  To start this quest from the beginning, follow these steps:<BR>
1. Get some brewing and smithing skill.<BR>
2. Hunt the Sarnak Crypt Raider to get his brain, then bank it.<BR>
3. Hunt Escaped Froglok Slaves and get 2 broken shackles.<BR>
4. Take the shackles to the Taskmaster to get Granite Pebbles. <BR>
5. Smith the pebbles into Bone Granite Powder.<BR>
6. Go make bog juice.<BR>
7. Brew the Embalming Fluid using the 2 juices, the powder, and rubbing alcohol.<BR>
8. Get the canopic from Rixiz, combine the brain and fluid, give it back with your second-rank skullcap and win the game.<BR>
Here's a hint: print out the original post for this quest so you can have it handy as you complete this quest.  Make notes and corrections and post them here.  Send me email too.
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
